This paper is about relation classification, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The paper proposes a novel model for relation classification and presents a new dataset for named entity recognition and relation classification in Chinese. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions reducing the complexity of the model, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
